sample_extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was isolated with Trizol (Invitrogen Cat. No. 15596-026, Carlsbad, CA), according to the manufacturer's instructions. Total RNA was further purified using the Qiagen RNAeasy Mini Kit (Cat. No. 74104) according to the manufacturer's instructions
sample_extract_protocol_ch2: Total RNA was isolated with Trizol (Invitrogen Cat. No. 15596-026, Carlsbad, CA), according to the manufacturer's instructions. Total RNA was further purified using the Qiagen RNAeasy Mini Kit (Cat. No. 74104) according to the manufacturer's instructions
sample_label_protocol_ch1: One ug of total RNA was reverse transcripted to cDNA using T7 Promoter Primer and MMLV-RT. Then the cDNA was converted to aRNA using T7 RNA polymerase, which simultaneously amplifies target material and incorporates cyanine 3- or cyanine 5-labeled CTP (Two-Color Microarray-Based Gene Expression Analysis Protocol, Agilent).
sample_label_protocol_ch2: One ug of total RNA was reverse transcripted to cDNA using T7 Promoter Primer and MMLV-RT. Then the cDNA was converted to aRNA using T7 RNA polymerase, which simultaneously amplifies target material and incorporates cyanine 3- or cyanine 5-labeled CTP (Two-Color Microarray-Based Gene Expression Analysis Protocol, Agilent).
sample_data_processing: Images were auto gridded, analyzed and data extracted using Agilent Feature Extraction Software (Version 9.1.3.1).  Spot values were normalized using the default linear-lowess normalization. LogRatio for all probes, which were used for subsequent analysis, were converted to log(2). Although the 1x44k and 4x44k arrays have the same probes, the 4x44k arrays have 10 replicates of some probes. Thus, to generate a final data set, the median value of replicated probes was used for 4x44k arrays. The fi ...
sample_hyb_protocol: 825ng of Cy3 and Cy5 labelled aRNA were hybridized competitively for 17 hrs in a 65 C hybridization oven (G2545A, Agilent) set to 10 rpm in a final concentration of 1X GEx Hybridization Buffer HI-RPM, according to the manufacturer's recommnded protocol (Two-Color Microarray-Based Gene Expression Analysis, Agilent). Arrays were washed according to the manufacturer's recommended protocol including the Stabilization and Drying Solution step (Two-Color Microarray-Based Gene Expression Analysis, Agil ...

sample_label_protocol_ch2: One ug of total RNA was reverse transcripted to cDNA using T7 Promoter Primer and MMLV-RT. Then the cDNA was converted to aRNA using T7 RNA polymerase, which simultaneously amplifies target material and incorporates cyanine 3- or cyanine 5-labeled CTP (Two-Color Microarray-Based Gene Expression Analysis Protocol, Agilent).
sample_data_processing: Images were auto gridded, analyzed and data extracted using Agilent Feature Extraction Software (Version 9.1.3.1).  Spot values were normalized using the default linear-lowess normalization. LogRatio for all probes, which were used for subsequent analysis, were converted to log(2). Although the 1x44k and 4x44k arrays have the same probes, the 4x44k arrays have 10 replicates of some probes. Thus, to generate a final data set, the median value of replicated probes was used for 4x44k arrays. The fi ...
sample_hyb_protocol: 825ng of Cy3 and Cy5 labelled aRNA were hybridized competitively for 17 hrs in a 65 C hybridization oven (G2545A, Agilent) set to 10 rpm in a final concentration of 1X GEx Hybridization Buffer HI-RPM, according to the manufacturer's recommnded protocol (Two-Color Microarray-Based Gene Expression Analysis, Agilent). Arrays were washed according to the manufacturer's recommended protocol including the Stabilization and Drying Solution step (Two-Color Microarray-Based Gene Expression Analysis, Agil ...

Then the cDNA was converted to aRNA using T7 RNA polymerase, which simultaneously amplifies target material and incorporates cyanine 3- or cyanine 5-labeled CTP (Two-Color Microarray-Based Gene Expression Analysis Protocol, Agilent).
sample_label_protocol_ch2: One ug of total RNA was reverse transcripted to cDNA using T7 Promoter Primer and MMLV-RT. sample_data_processing: Images were auto gridded, analyzed and data extracted using Agilent Feature Extraction Software (Version 9.1.3.1).  Spot values were normalized using the default linear-lowess normalization. LogRatio for all probes, which were used for subsequent analysis, were converted to log(2). Although the 1x44k and 4x44k arrays have the same probes, the 4x44k arrays have 10 replicates of some probes. Thus, to generate a final data set, the median value of replicated probes was used for 4x44k arrays. The fi ...
sample_hyb_protocol: 825ng of Cy3 and Cy5 labelled aRNA were hybridized competitively for 17 hrs in a 65 C hybridization oven (G2545A, Agilent) set to 10 rpm in a final concentration of 1X GEx Hybridization Buffer HI-RPM, according to the manufacturer's recommnded protocol (Two-Color Microarray-Based Gene Expression Analysis, Agilent). sample_data_processing: Images were auto gridded, analyzed and data extracted using Agilent Feature Extraction Software (Version 9.1.3.1).  Spot values were normalized using the default linear-lowess normalization. LogRatio for all probes, which were used for subsequent analysis, were converted to log(2). Although the 1x44k and 4x44k arrays have the same probes, the 4x44k arrays have 10 replicates of some probes. Thus, to generate a final data set, the median value of replicated probes was used for 4x44k arrays. The fi ...

sample_extract_protocol_ch1: gDNA was isolated using the Qiagen DNeasy Blood & Tissue Kit according to the manufacturer’s instructions.

sample_label_protocol_ch1: 1.5 - 3 ug of gDNA from prostate specimens (test channel) or Human Male Genomic DNA (Promega, reference channel), was restriction digested with AluI and RsaI, and labeled with Cy-5 (test channel) or Cy-3 (reference channel).
sample_label_protocol_ch2: 1.5 - 3 ug of gDNA from prostate specimens (test channel) or Human Male Genomic DNA (Promega, reference channel), was restriction digested with AluI and RsaI, and labeled with Cy-5 (test channel) or Cy-3 (reference channel).
sample_data_processing: Images were auto gridded, analyzed and data extracted using Agilent Feature Extraction Software (v9.5) using protocol CGH-v4_95_Feb07.  For data analysis, probes on all arrays were limited to those on the 105K array. Log(2) ratios for each probe were determined as rProcessedSignal/gProcessedSignal. To remove copy number variants, all probes with log(2) values >1 or <-1 in any of the 28 benign prostate samples were excluded. The final dataset (consisting of localized prostate cancer and castrate  ...
sample_hyb_protocol: Cy-5 (test channel) and Cy-3 (reference channel) labeled DNA was purified using Microcon YM-30 columns and hybridized for 40 hours at 65o C. Post-hybridization wash was performed with acetonitrile wash and Agilent Stabilization and Drying Solution wash.

sample_data_processing: Images were auto gridded, analyzed and data extracted using Agilent Feature Extraction Software (v9.5) using protocol CGH-v4_95_Feb07.  For data analysis, probes on all arrays were limited to those on the 105K array. Log(2) ratios for each probe were determined as rProcessedSignal/gProcessedSignal. To remove copy number variants, all probes with log(2) values >1 or <-1 in any of the 28 benign prostate samples were excluded. sample_data_processing: Images were auto gridded, analyzed and data extracted using Agilent Feature Extraction Software (v9.5) using protocol CGH-v4_95_Feb07.  For data analysis, probes on all arrays were limited to those on the 105K array. Log(2) ratios for each probe were determined as rProcessedSignal/gProcessedSignal. To remove copy number variants, all probes with log(2) values >1 or <-1 in any of the 28 benign prostate samples were excluded. The final dataset (consisting of localized prostate cancer and castrate  ...
sample_hyb_protocol: Cy-5 (test channel) and Cy-3 (reference channel) labeled DNA was purified using Microcon YM-30 columns and hybridized for 40 hours at 65o C. Post-hybridization wash was performed with acetonitrile wash and Agilent Stabilization and Drying Solution wash.

sample_label_protocol_ch1: 1.5 - 3 ug of gDNA from prostate specimens (test channel) or Human Male Genomic DNA (Promega, reference channel), was restriction digested with AluI and RsaI, and labeled with Cy-5 (test channel) or Cy-3 (reference channel).
sample_source_name_ch2: metastatic prostate cancer (obtained at rapid [warm] autopsy)
sample_characteristics_ch2: tissue: metastatic castrate resistant prostate cancer (WA)
sample_label_protocol_ch2: 1.5 - 3 ug of gDNA from prostate specimens (test channel) or Human Male Genomic DNA (Promega, reference channel), was restriction digested with AluI and RsaI, and labeled with Cy-5 (test channel) or Cy-3 (reference channel).
sample_data_processing: Images were auto gridded, analyzed and data extracted using Agilent Feature Extraction Software (v9.5) using protocol CGH-v4_95_Feb07.  For data analysis, probes on all arrays were limited to those on the 105K array. Log(2) ratios for each probe were determined as rProcessedSignal/gProcessedSignal. To remove copy number variants, all probes with log(2) values >1 or <-1 in any of the 28 benign prostate samples were excluded. sample_hyb_protocol: Cy-5 (test channel) and Cy-3 (reference channel) labeled DNA was purified using Microcon YM-30 columns and hybridized for 40 hours at 65o C. Post-hybridization wash was performed with acetonitrile wash and Agilent Stabilization and Drying Solution wash.
